10 §694. Group health insurance; Thirtieth Judicial District; office of the district
11 attorney; eligible retired employees
12 A. The premium costs of group health insurance shall be paid in full from
13 the district attorney's general fund of the Thirtieth Judicial District, or by paying an
14 amount equal to one hundred percent of the premium for a current employee of the
15 office of the district attorney, as the retiree chooses, for any district attorney or
16 assistant district attorney who retired with at least twenty-four years of full-time
17 service, regardless of age.
18 B. When the retired district attorney or assistant district attorney reaches the
19 age or condition for Medicare eligibility, the retired district attorney or assistant
20 district attorney shall secure Medicare and pursue a supplemental plan. The office
21 of the district attorney shall continue to pay the retired district attorney's or assistant
22 district attorney's current health insurance premium or the premium for the
23 supplemental plan that is comparable to the present insurance coverage.
24 C. As used in this Section, "years of full-time service" means the number of
25 years of creditable service that the retiree had in the District Attorneys' Retirement
26 System, as an assistant district attorney or an elected district attorney."
